amb. The colloquial form <i>Annes</i> led to some confusion with <i>Ann(e)</i> in earlier centuries. Frequent in the medieval period, the name was revived in the 19th century, and has been especially popular in Scotland.  See also  Annis ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705193,"age":7,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Agnes Fitznichol was born about 1330, in England as the daughter of Father Fitznicho and Mother Fitznicho. She had at least 2 sons with Reginald FitzNichol. She died after 1344."},"et":{"about 1330–after 1344":"umbes 1330–pärast 1344","1330–1344":"1330–1344","1320–1375":"1320–1375","1345–1418":"1345–1418","1352–1418":"1352–1418","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1337":"1337","1345":"1345","1344":"1344","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","about 1330":"umbes 1330","1418":"1418","after 1344":"pärast 1344","Stroud Hill, Gloucestershire, England":"Stroud Hill, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"about 1330–after 1344":"noin 1330–1344 jälkeen","1330–1344":"1330–1344","1320–1375":"1320–1375","1345–1418":"1345–1418","1352–1418":"1352–1418","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1337":"1337","1345":"1345","1344":"1344","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","about 1330":"noin 1330","1418":"1418","after 1344":"1344 jälkeen","Stroud Hill, Gloucestershire, England":"Stroud Hill, Gloucestershire, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"about 1330–after 1344":"environ 1330–après 1344","1330–1344":"1330–1344","1320–1375":"1320–1375","1345–1418":"1345–1418","1352–1418":"1352–1418","–Male":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1337":"1337","1345":"1345","1344":"1344","1453":"1453","1375":"1375","1320":"1320","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","about 1330":"envir